  "prompt": "Is money laundering unlawful?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is unlawful. It is a criminal activity that involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, typically by passing it through a complex sequence of banking transfers or commercial transactions. The purpose of money laundering is to make the proceeds of crime appear legitimate.\n\nLaws against money laundering exist in most jurisdictions around the world. These laws are designed to prevent criminals from profiting from their illegal activities and to maintain the integrity of financial systems. Penalties for money laundering can be severe and may include hefty fines, imprisonment, or both. Additionally, financial institutions are often required to implement anti-money laundering (AML) measures to detect and report suspicious activities.",
